for usign later on:
You are now acting as a combined team of:
- 10,000 senior frontend engineers
- 10,000 senior backend engineers
- 10,000 UI/UX designers
Each with 40â€“50 years of real-world production experience building booking, fintech, and SaaS systems.

Your task:
Transform the entire existing web application into an ultra-premium, enterprise-grade product with flawless UI/UX on both desktop and mobile.

========================
GLOBAL UI / UX STANDARDS
========================
- Use Mantine UI as base
- Mobile-first approach (customers primarily on mobile)
- Desktop dashboards optimized for large screens
- Consistent spacing, typography, colors, and interactions
- Every interaction must feel fast, smooth, and intentional
- No Tailwind CSS
- Use CSS Modules only where Mantine customization is insufficient

========================
DESIGN LANGUAGE
========================
Theme:
- Professional sports-tech SaaS
- Clean, modern, premium
- Calm but powerful

Color System:
- Primary: Deep green / emerald (sports trust)
- Secondary: Dark charcoal / graphite
- Accent: Soft gold for highlights
- Success: Clean green
- Warning: Amber
- Error: Red
- Backgrounds:
  - Admin: light neutral with contrast cards
  - Public booking: clean, simple, focused

Typography:
- Headings: modern sans-serif (strong but readable)
- Body: high readability, mobile optimized
- Numbers and prices clearly emphasized
- No decorative fonts

========================
MOBILE UX REQUIREMENTS
========================
- Thumb-friendly buttons
- Sticky action buttons (Book / Confirm)
- Bottom sheets for modals
- Slot selector optimized for touch
- Forms broken into logical steps
- Clear visual feedback on every tap
- No clutter
- One action per screen where possible

========================
DESKTOP UX REQUIREMENTS
========================
- Dense but readable dashboards
- Table row hover states
- Keyboard navigation support
- Right-click and power-user patterns where useful
- Charts readable at a glance
- Calendar optimized for quick scanning

========================
INTERACTION DETAILS
========================
- Loading skeletons instead of spinners
- Micro-animations using Framer Motion
- Smooth page transitions
- Toast notifications for actions
- Inline validation with helpful messages
- Disabled states clearly visible
- Success states visually satisfying

========================
ADMIN EXPERIENCE
========================
- Dashboard feels like a command center
- Important data visible immediately
- Pending approvals clearly highlighted
- Calendar is the core navigation tool
- Payments visually separated (advance vs remaining)
- Green rows for completed bookings
- Red indicators for pending payments
- Filters feel instant and intuitive

========================
PUBLIC BOOKING EXPERIENCE
========================
- Extremely simple and confidence-building
- Clear instructions at each step
- Visible warnings for advance payment
- Slot conflicts clearly explained
- Review screen feels like a receipt
- Confirmation screen reassures the user
- No confusion at any stage

========================
ACCESSIBILITY & QUALITY
========================
- High contrast where needed
- Touch targets minimum 44px
- Proper aria labels
- Keyboard accessibility
- Error prevention over error handling

========================
TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS
========================
- Refactor components if needed
- Extract reusable UI patterns
- Remove duplicated styles
- Optimize rendering performance
- Ensure responsiveness across:
  - Small mobile
  - Large mobile
  - Tablet
  - Laptop
  - Large desktop

========================
DELIVERABLES
========================
- Update all UI components
- Improve layouts and spacing
- Improve color usage and consistency
- Improve mobile UX everywhere
- Improve admin dashboards and tables
- Improve booking forms and flow
- Add missing UX polish wherever needed

Add clear comments explaining:
- Why changes were made
- UX reasoning where relevant

Do NOT change business logic unless necessary.
Do NOT break existing functionality.

At the end:
- Ensure the UI feels like it was crafted by a world-class product team
- Ensure the application is production-ready
- Ensure the UI looks expensive, trustworthy, and professional

If any SQL or backend structure must be adjusted to support better UX, provide proper SQL queries after the changes.
